WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.840 align:middle line:90%


00:00:07.840 --> 00:00:11.760 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:11.760 --> 00:00:20.377 align:middle line:90%


00:00:20.377 --> 00:00:21.960 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA MEREDITH:
I have often asked,

00:00:21.960 --> 00:00:23.610 align:middle line:10%
where are the
great philosophers,

00:00:23.610 --> 00:00:25.770 align:middle line:10%
now that we really,
really need them?

00:00:25.770 --> 00:00:28.770 align:middle line:84%
And I've often thought, probably
reincarnated on Wall Street

00:00:28.770 --> 00:00:32.640 align:middle line:84%
after starving to death in their
past life as a philosopher.

00:00:32.640 --> 00:00:33.660 align:middle line:90%
Or maybe not--

00:00:33.660 --> 00:00:35.640 align:middle line:84%
Tim Freke is a
modern-day philosopher.

00:00:35.640 --> 00:00:38.280 align:middle line:84%
And he is making the bigger
vision of who and what we are

00:00:38.280 --> 00:00:41.160 align:middle line:84%
as human beings both
entertaining and approachable,

00:00:41.160 --> 00:00:44.460 align:middle line:84%
because we cannot afford to
continue avoiding looking

00:00:44.460 --> 00:00:47.610 align:middle line:84%
at what we are and what
we're contributing to life,

00:00:47.610 --> 00:00:50.900 align:middle line:84%
to this planet,
and to the cosmos.

00:00:50.900 --> 00:00:52.890 align:middle line:84%
We've got to start
looking at ourselves,

00:00:52.890 --> 00:00:55.440 align:middle line:84%
looking at our motives, and
that's what you guys are paid--

00:00:55.440 --> 00:00:56.460 align:middle line:90%
or not paid--

00:00:56.460 --> 00:00:57.960 align:middle line:90%
to do.

00:00:57.960 --> 00:00:59.790 align:middle line:90%
>>TIM FREKE: Yeah.

00:00:59.790 --> 00:01:02.465 align:middle line:84%
Ultimately, everything comes
from what we think this is.

00:01:02.465 --> 00:01:03.340 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:01:03.340 --> 00:01:04.890 align:middle line:84%
But nobody's really
thinking about that

00:01:04.890 --> 00:01:05.900 align:middle line:90%
except the philosophers.

00:01:05.900 --> 00:01:06.700 align:middle line:90%
>>FREKE: I know.

00:01:06.700 --> 00:01:09.480 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: When my son chose
to major in philosophy,

00:01:09.480 --> 00:01:12.650 align:middle line:84%
everyone else was so
oh, I'm so sorry, right,

00:01:12.650 --> 00:01:14.250 align:middle line:90%
knowing he'd starve to death.

00:01:14.250 --> 00:01:15.510 align:middle line:90%
But you know what?

00:01:15.510 --> 00:01:19.140 align:middle line:84%
We need philosophers
right now to really start

00:01:19.140 --> 00:01:24.060 align:middle line:84%
considering what the stage of
our evolution is as a species

00:01:24.060 --> 00:01:27.072 align:middle line:84%
and what we can do with this,
where we can go with it.

00:01:27.072 --> 00:01:29.280 align:middle line:84%
And that's really what you're
charging yourself with.

00:01:29.280 --> 00:01:30.113 align:middle line:90%
>>FREKE: Absolutely.

00:01:30.113 --> 00:01:33.000 align:middle line:10%
It feels like a
lot of people feel

00:01:33.000 --> 00:01:34.980 align:middle line:10%
that humanity's lost its way--

00:01:34.980 --> 00:01:35.780 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: It has--

00:01:35.780 --> 00:01:39.720 align:middle line:10%
>>FREKE: And I-- yeah,
because the choice on offer

00:01:39.720 --> 00:01:43.560 align:middle line:10%
traditionally now or it has been
between religion, which often

00:01:43.560 --> 00:01:45.150 align:middle line:10%
seems irrational, outdated.

00:01:45.150 --> 00:01:47.130 align:middle line:84%
It's kind of we don't
think the universe was

00:01:47.130 --> 00:01:48.840 align:middle line:90%
collated in seven days anymore.

00:01:48.840 --> 00:01:50.348 align:middle line:90%
We've done that.

00:01:50.348 --> 00:01:52.140 align:middle line:84%
And then we've got this
new thing, science,

00:01:52.140 --> 00:01:54.880 align:middle line:84%
which is so powerful
but literally soulless.

00:01:54.880 --> 00:01:57.555 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't speak to the
meaning of what life is.

00:01:57.555 --> 00:01:59.430 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It doesn't
speak to anyone's heart.

00:01:59.430 --> 00:02:00.810 align:middle line:90%
>>FREKE: It doesn't.

00:02:00.810 --> 00:02:04.410 align:middle line:84%
I have a huge respect for
it, but it only goes so far.

00:02:04.410 --> 00:02:07.580 align:middle line:84%
And then we're
looking for what's

00:02:07.580 --> 00:02:09.900 align:middle line:84%
going to fill that
hole in the middle.

00:02:09.900 --> 00:02:15.000 align:middle line:84%
And I've been exploring
spirituality all my life,

00:02:15.000 --> 00:02:17.070 align:middle line:90%
from a very young age.

00:02:17.070 --> 00:02:20.610 align:middle line:84%
And as I've got older,
I've wondered, how can we

00:02:20.610 --> 00:02:24.540 align:middle line:84%
get to the essence of this and
then frame it in such a way

00:02:24.540 --> 00:02:28.740 align:middle line:84%
that it doesn't become
on the edges of culture?

00:02:28.740 --> 00:02:30.210 align:middle line:84%
It can come right
into the middle,

00:02:30.210 --> 00:02:33.390 align:middle line:90%
and it can speak to science.

00:02:33.390 --> 00:02:35.970 align:middle line:84%
So scientific knowledge
of spiritual wisdom

00:02:35.970 --> 00:02:38.640 align:middle line:84%
can become part of
one thing, rather than

00:02:38.640 --> 00:02:39.880 align:middle line:90%
seemingly in opposition.

00:02:39.880 --> 00:02:40.680 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:02:40.680 --> 00:02:45.270 align:middle line:84%
And there are a number of
people, aside from yourself,

00:02:45.270 --> 00:02:47.540 align:middle line:84%
who are also charging
themselves with this.

00:02:47.540 --> 00:02:51.120 align:middle line:84%
And we need an army
of philosophers

00:02:51.120 --> 00:02:55.050 align:middle line:84%
that can speak the language
of any different demographic

00:02:55.050 --> 00:02:57.100 align:middle line:84%
and to each culture
of the world.

00:02:57.100 --> 00:02:59.130 align:middle line:84%
So there are many
ways to frame this.

00:02:59.130 --> 00:03:01.390 align:middle line:84%
>>FREKE: Not only
many ways to frame it,

00:03:01.390 --> 00:03:03.340 align:middle line:90%
but also, it's not easy.

00:03:03.340 --> 00:03:04.140 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:03:04.140 --> 00:03:05.807 align:middle line:84%
>>FREKE: That's why
it hasn't been done.

00:03:05.807 --> 00:03:06.720 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:03:06.720 --> 00:03:09.000 align:middle line:10%
>>FREKE: Go back to Einstein
and great scientists,

00:03:09.000 --> 00:03:12.210 align:middle line:10%
Niels Bohr, the people who've
created modern science.

00:03:12.210 --> 00:03:14.640 align:middle line:10%
And they also felt that
bringing these two things

00:03:14.640 --> 00:03:16.873 align:middle line:10%
together was the great
intellectual challenge

00:03:16.873 --> 00:03:18.540 align:middle line:10%
of our time, because
it would completely

00:03:18.540 --> 00:03:21.750 align:middle line:10%
change how we see reality and
then how we live our lives.

00:03:21.750 --> 00:03:23.035 align:middle line:90%
But it's not easy to do.

00:03:23.035 --> 00:03:24.660 align:middle line:84%
There are challenges
to make it happen.

00:03:24.660 --> 00:03:25.150 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's not easy to do.

00:03:25.150 --> 00:03:26.790 align:middle line:84%
And so now we're
in an environment--

00:03:26.790 --> 00:03:29.172 align:middle line:84%
I interviewed Rupert
Sheldrake about a year ago.

00:03:29.172 --> 00:03:30.130 align:middle line:10%
>>FREKE: Great example.

00:03:30.130 --> 00:03:31.880 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: Yeah, he's
a good example of it.

00:03:31.880 --> 00:03:34.200 align:middle line:10%
And in the newest
book he had written,

00:03:34.200 --> 00:03:35.960 align:middle line:10%
we were talking
about the statistics

00:03:35.960 --> 00:03:38.250 align:middle line:10%
in it, that the world is now--

00:03:38.250 --> 00:03:42.690 align:middle line:10%
England, in
particular, but also,

00:03:42.690 --> 00:03:45.660 align:middle line:10%
actually surprisingly,
the US less so.

00:03:45.660 --> 00:03:48.180 align:middle line:84%
But all of the Western
world is really now

00:03:48.180 --> 00:03:51.547 align:middle line:90%
in a state of majority atheist.

00:03:51.547 --> 00:03:52.380 align:middle line:90%
>>FREKE: Definitely.

00:03:52.380 --> 00:03:55.420 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And in England,
I think it's only--

00:03:55.420 --> 00:03:57.810 align:middle line:84%
oh gosh, it's something
like 80%, 85%.

00:03:57.810 --> 00:04:00.180 align:middle line:90%
>>FREKE: Definitely--

00:04:00.180 --> 00:04:01.560 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Which is interesting.

00:04:01.560 --> 00:04:02.550 align:middle line:84%
>>FREKE: I'm
optimistic about that.

00:04:02.550 --> 00:04:02.800 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:04:02.800 --> 00:04:04.290 align:middle line:84%
And when I say
"atheism," I'm not

00:04:04.290 --> 00:04:06.373 align:middle line:84%
talking about going back
to fundamental religions.

00:04:06.373 --> 00:04:07.290 align:middle line:90%
>>FREKE: It's secular.

00:04:07.290 --> 00:04:08.310 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's secular.

00:04:08.310 --> 00:04:12.630 align:middle line:84%
And there's no purchase
in anything unseen.

00:04:12.630 --> 00:04:15.450 align:middle line:84%
Basically, it's more based
on scientific materialism,

00:04:15.450 --> 00:04:17.640 align:middle line:84%
although there is a kind
of spirituality that

00:04:17.640 --> 00:04:20.670 align:middle line:84%
can emerge alongside it
and can rise out of it.

00:04:20.670 --> 00:04:24.248 align:middle line:84%
But mostly, it's a materialistic
engagement with life.

00:04:24.248 --> 00:04:26.040 align:middle line:84%
>>FREKE: There's massive
wonder in science.

00:04:26.040 --> 00:04:28.218 align:middle line:84%
And there are lots
of TV programs--

00:04:28.218 --> 00:04:29.760 align:middle line:84%
in England, Brian
Cox and people like

00:04:29.760 --> 00:04:30.770 align:middle line:84%
this-- who are looking
at the universe

00:04:30.770 --> 00:04:31.590 align:middle line:90%
and go, look at the wonder.

00:04:31.590 --> 00:04:32.430 align:middle line:90%
Look at the wonder.

00:04:32.430 --> 00:04:34.380 align:middle line:90%
And god, it is wonderful.

00:04:34.380 --> 00:04:38.370 align:middle line:84%
But the small print with
that philosophy is oh,

00:04:38.370 --> 00:04:40.740 align:middle line:84%
but by the way,
you're a clever monkey

00:04:40.740 --> 00:04:42.750 align:middle line:84%
clinging to a rock
for a few short years.

00:04:42.750 --> 00:04:43.800 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And all
this is random.

00:04:43.800 --> 00:04:45.820 align:middle line:84%
>>FREKE: And then there's
no purpose to your life,

00:04:45.820 --> 00:04:46.280 align:middle line:90%
and you're gone.

00:04:46.280 --> 00:04:47.080 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:04:47.080 --> 00:04:48.990 align:middle line:84%
>>FREKE: So that's a
very, very bleak view--

00:04:48.990 --> 00:04:49.470 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's very bleak--

00:04:49.470 --> 00:04:51.270 align:middle line:84%
>>FREKE: Which pushes
people into a kind

00:04:51.270 --> 00:04:54.090 align:middle line:90%
of short-term materialism.

00:04:54.090 --> 00:04:56.680 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yes, and which I
think is where we are right now.

00:04:56.680 --> 00:04:57.110 align:middle line:90%
>>FREKE: It is.

00:04:57.110 --> 00:04:57.910 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:04:57.910 --> 00:05:02.500 align:middle line:84%
>>FREKE: But because I'm an
evolutionist, I think it's OK.

00:05:02.500 --> 00:05:07.650 align:middle line:84%
I think what's happening is
that this very limited but deep

00:05:07.650 --> 00:05:11.520 align:middle line:84%
materialist science has cleared
away a previous phase, where

00:05:11.520 --> 00:05:13.200 align:middle line:84%
we were superstitious
and irrational.

00:05:13.200 --> 00:05:15.220 align:middle line:84%
And it's true because it's in
the book and all that stuff.

00:05:15.220 --> 00:05:16.980 align:middle line:84%
So that's cleared
away, especially not

00:05:16.980 --> 00:05:19.510 align:middle line:84%
so much in the US but
definitely Europe.

00:05:19.510 --> 00:05:21.410 align:middle line:90%
And then it doesn't stop there.

00:05:21.410 --> 00:05:23.260 align:middle line:84%
Now, what we need
is the next phase.

00:05:23.260 --> 00:05:26.450 align:middle line:84%
And what I think can come next
is a rational spirituality.

00:05:26.450 --> 00:05:27.250 align:middle line:90%
And by "rational."

00:05:27.250 --> 00:05:30.280 align:middle line:84%
I just mean that it's
actually trans-rational.

00:05:30.280 --> 00:05:31.920 align:middle line:90%
It embraces thinking clearly.

00:05:31.920 --> 00:05:32.680 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You mean "explicable."

00:05:32.680 --> 00:05:32.980 align:middle line:90%
>>FREKE: Yeah.

00:05:32.980 --> 00:05:34.060 align:middle line:90%
It thinks clearly.

00:05:34.060 --> 00:05:35.950 align:middle line:84%
It asks questions,
and it believes

00:05:35.950 --> 00:05:37.153 align:middle line:90%
things for good reasons.

00:05:37.153 --> 00:05:39.820 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But you almost have to
go through that painful process

00:05:39.820 --> 00:05:42.160 align:middle line:84%
of living through the
vacuum and finding out

00:05:42.160 --> 00:05:44.710 align:middle line:84%
how empty it is to just keep
filling our life with more

00:05:44.710 --> 00:05:45.250 align:middle line:90%
stuff.

00:05:45.250 --> 00:05:46.060 align:middle line:84%
>>FREKE: That's
what's happening.

00:05:46.060 --> 00:05:46.390 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:05:46.390 --> 00:05:48.100 align:middle line:84%
>>FREKE: And what
I see in the States

00:05:48.100 --> 00:05:49.570 align:middle line:90%
is that you have all of it.

00:05:49.570 --> 00:05:53.130 align:middle line:84%
You've still got the kind
of mythic religious stage.

00:05:53.130 --> 00:05:54.380 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Huge fundamentalism.

00:05:54.380 --> 00:05:55.930 align:middle line:84%
>>FREKE: Yeah, all
of that stronger

00:05:55.930 --> 00:05:59.200 align:middle line:84%
than we have it,
because it was involved

00:05:59.200 --> 00:06:00.460 align:middle line:90%
in forming the country.

00:06:00.460 --> 00:06:03.610 align:middle line:84%
And then there's this
wonderful secular science.

00:06:03.610 --> 00:06:04.870 align:middle line:90%
We're leading the world.

00:06:04.870 --> 00:06:06.840 align:middle line:84%
And then there's this
other thing growing,

00:06:06.840 --> 00:06:12.010 align:middle line:84%
particularly here, which is this
thoughtful, deep spirituality,

00:06:12.010 --> 00:06:13.360 align:middle line:90%
which I think's the future.

00:06:13.360 --> 00:06:14.590 align:middle line:90%
I think this is coming.

00:06:14.590 --> 00:06:17.470 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: How is this
happening for you in England?

00:06:17.470 --> 00:06:18.387 align:middle line:90%
How do people respond?

00:06:18.387 --> 00:06:20.678 align:middle line:84%
>>FREKE: We have less of the
problem of fundamentalism,

00:06:20.678 --> 00:06:22.722 align:middle line:84%
and we have less of the
new thing coming through.

00:06:22.722 --> 00:06:23.680 align:middle line:90%
Or how do they respond?

00:06:23.680 --> 00:06:23.890 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:06:23.890 --> 00:06:26.620 align:middle line:84%
How do they respond to you,
to these messages in England

00:06:26.620 --> 00:06:29.200 align:middle line:90%
and Europe in particular?

00:06:29.200 --> 00:06:32.350 align:middle line:84%
>>FREKE: For my own experiences,
I have a fantastic response.

00:06:32.350 --> 00:06:40.870 align:middle line:84%
And I believe that is because
what I try to do is honor--

00:06:40.870 --> 00:06:43.133 align:middle line:90%
I'm not putting down science.

00:06:43.133 --> 00:06:44.800 align:middle line:84%
I'm going, look,
there's something more.

00:06:44.800 --> 00:06:47.620 align:middle line:84%
And if I do it in a
clear way and I do it

00:06:47.620 --> 00:06:51.610 align:middle line:84%
in a way which makes sense to
people's actual experience,

00:06:51.610 --> 00:06:52.600 align:middle line:90%
people pick up on it.

00:06:52.600 --> 00:06:52.950 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:06:52.950 --> 00:06:54.190 align:middle line:84%
>>FREKE: And what I'm
loving is especially

00:06:54.190 --> 00:06:55.870 align:middle line:90%
sharing that with young people.

00:06:55.870 --> 00:06:58.480 align:middle line:84%
Often, people are
scientists, young scientists,

00:06:58.480 --> 00:07:00.710 align:middle line:84%
who are going, actually,
what you're saying,

00:07:00.710 --> 00:07:02.050 align:middle line:90%
that actually makes sense.

00:07:02.050 --> 00:07:04.083 align:middle line:90%
And that's really exciting.

00:07:04.083 --> 00:07:06.250 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Do you find that
in dealing with a younger

00:07:06.250 --> 00:07:09.310 align:middle line:84%
generation that is now coming up
through the educational system

00:07:09.310 --> 00:07:12.340 align:middle line:84%
and so forth,
millennials and younger,

00:07:12.340 --> 00:07:16.413 align:middle line:84%
there is a different type
of language or yearning

00:07:16.413 --> 00:07:18.580 align:middle line:84%
that's occurring that really
is almost becoming more

00:07:18.580 --> 00:07:22.990 align:middle line:84%
heart-centered, being driven
by a more heart-centered need

00:07:22.990 --> 00:07:25.610 align:middle line:84%
to connect, to connect
not just the pieces,

00:07:25.610 --> 00:07:27.260 align:middle line:84%
but also to connect
with each other,

00:07:27.260 --> 00:07:29.500 align:middle line:84%
to connect with the planet,
just more heart-centered?

00:07:29.500 --> 00:07:30.300 align:middle line:90%
>>FREKE: Yeah.

00:07:30.300 --> 00:07:32.920 align:middle line:90%


00:07:32.920 --> 00:07:36.160 align:middle line:84%
People often--
mistakenly, in my view--

00:07:36.160 --> 00:07:38.350 align:middle line:84%
see the growth of social
media and the internet

00:07:38.350 --> 00:07:40.382 align:middle line:90%
as about lack of connection.

00:07:40.382 --> 00:07:42.340 align:middle line:84%
I'm looking at it with
the young people I know,

00:07:42.340 --> 00:07:44.303 align:middle line:90%
and they're totally connected.

00:07:44.303 --> 00:07:45.970 align:middle line:84%
They're connected
when they're together.

00:07:45.970 --> 00:07:47.360 align:middle line:84%
They're connected when
they're not together.

00:07:47.360 --> 00:07:47.980 align:middle line:90%
They're just connected.

00:07:47.980 --> 00:07:50.050 align:middle line:84%
And it feels like, oh, we're
entering the age of connection.

00:07:50.050 --> 00:07:51.440 align:middle line:90%
Well, actually, we're in it.

00:07:51.440 --> 00:07:55.150 align:middle line:84%
And if we can understand
it well enough,

00:07:55.150 --> 00:07:58.060 align:middle line:84%
if we can articulate these
deep perennial spiritual truths

00:07:58.060 --> 00:08:05.440 align:middle line:84%
in a new way for our own
time, then I think very soon,

00:08:05.440 --> 00:08:08.770 align:middle line:84%
this new thing will
start to emerge.

00:08:08.770 --> 00:08:11.990 align:middle line:84%
My own feeling--
maybe it's too much.

00:08:11.990 --> 00:08:12.790 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:08:12.790 --> 00:08:14.810 align:middle line:84%
But my own intuition,
for what it's worth,

00:08:14.810 --> 00:08:16.352 align:middle line:84%
is that this new
understanding that's

00:08:16.352 --> 00:08:20.050 align:middle line:84%
coming, that I'm trying to be
a part of and so many of us,

00:08:20.050 --> 00:08:21.640 align:middle line:84%
I think it will
be as big a shift

00:08:21.640 --> 00:08:24.090 align:middle line:84%
for human culture as
the evolution of science

00:08:24.090 --> 00:08:25.643 align:middle line:90%
was 400 years ago.

00:08:25.643 --> 00:08:26.810 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I should think so.

00:08:26.810 --> 00:08:29.268 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: And if you look back
now and imagine taking Isaac

00:08:29.268 --> 00:08:33.730 align:middle line:10%
Newton or any of those founding
individuals of that and showing

00:08:33.730 --> 00:08:34.990 align:middle line:10%
them this--

00:08:34.990 --> 00:08:39.880 align:middle line:10%
the internet, Gaia TV, me
flying in in a great big metal

00:08:39.880 --> 00:08:42.220 align:middle line:10%
box from England across
the Atlantic Ocean--

00:08:42.220 --> 00:08:45.172 align:middle line:10%
these are unthinkable things,
which we take for granted.

00:08:45.172 --> 00:08:46.880 align:middle line:84%
And I think that a
bigger jump will come.

00:08:46.880 --> 00:08:48.630 align:middle line:84%
But it's not going to
be about technology.

00:08:48.630 --> 00:08:50.290 align:middle line:84%
That's a continuation
of the old thing.

00:08:50.290 --> 00:08:50.770 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:08:50.770 --> 00:08:52.280 align:middle line:84%
>>FREKE: It's going
to be about what

00:08:52.280 --> 00:08:55.810 align:middle line:84%
we see this is, what we
see life actually is,

00:08:55.810 --> 00:08:58.877 align:middle line:84%
and what we see death is and
what we see meaning is about.

00:08:58.877 --> 00:09:00.460 align:middle line:84%
These are the things
I think will just

00:09:00.460 --> 00:09:03.920 align:middle line:84%
transform our vision of
what it is to be human.

00:09:03.920 --> 00:09:06.760 align:middle line:84%
And then once that changes,
our behavior will change.

00:09:06.760 --> 00:09:07.480 align:middle line:84%
And then a whole
new world opens up.

00:09:07.480 --> 00:09:09.397 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yes, because
the underpinnings of it

00:09:09.397 --> 00:09:12.160 align:middle line:84%
is to begin exploring the
true nature of reality,

00:09:12.160 --> 00:09:16.420 align:middle line:84%
but understanding it from a
psychospiritual point of view,

00:09:16.420 --> 00:09:19.750 align:middle line:84%
the true nature of reality and
how all of this comes together

00:09:19.750 --> 00:09:21.465 align:middle line:84%
and functions and
works to begin with,

00:09:21.465 --> 00:09:23.590 align:middle line:84%
which takes an incredibly
open mind, meaning people

00:09:23.590 --> 00:09:28.960 align:middle line:84%
have to start really cutting
from the dogma of both science

00:09:28.960 --> 00:09:31.810 align:middle line:84%
and religion to be
able to be free enough

00:09:31.810 --> 00:09:33.700 align:middle line:90%
to bring those parts together.

00:09:33.700 --> 00:09:36.020 align:middle line:84%
And that's the problem we've
had so far is dogmatism.

00:09:36.020 --> 00:09:37.882 align:middle line:84%
And we've just
been experiencing,

00:09:37.882 --> 00:09:40.090 align:middle line:84%
as we go through this really
critical point, a little

00:09:40.090 --> 00:09:43.680 align:middle line:84%
more dogmatism lately on
both sides, drawing apart.

00:09:43.680 --> 00:09:48.250 align:middle line:84%
>>FREKE: I've been recently
with some absolutely the

00:09:48.250 --> 00:09:50.620 align:middle line:90%
top neuroscientists.

00:09:50.620 --> 00:09:54.860 align:middle line:84%
And it's shocking at how
unsophisticated philosophically

00:09:54.860 --> 00:09:57.432 align:middle line:84%
they are, even though
they're brilliant scientists.

00:09:57.432 --> 00:09:58.390 align:middle line:90%
And the job has to be--

00:09:58.390 --> 00:09:59.932 align:middle line:84%
I feel like my job
in the middle here

00:09:59.932 --> 00:10:05.590 align:middle line:84%
is I'm asking science to keep
its essence, but to change.

00:10:05.590 --> 00:10:08.600 align:middle line:84%
And I'm asking spirituality to
keep its essence and to change.

00:10:08.600 --> 00:10:10.810 align:middle line:84%
And then I think we
can hold this together

00:10:10.810 --> 00:10:15.370 align:middle line:84%
with the biggest idea I think
that human beings have had

00:10:15.370 --> 00:10:17.960 align:middle line:84%
ever, which is
this understanding,

00:10:17.960 --> 00:10:21.300 align:middle line:84%
we now have that the whole
universe has evolved.

00:10:21.300 --> 00:10:24.210 align:middle line:84%
That's the foundation, I think,
to bring everything together.

00:10:24.210 --> 00:10:25.010 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Indeed.

00:10:25.010 --> 00:10:27.150 align:middle line:84%
And to that point, when
you're talking about some

00:10:27.150 --> 00:10:29.940 align:middle line:84%
of the new science
coming out, I experienced

00:10:29.940 --> 00:10:33.930 align:middle line:84%
something that was a really
wonderfully bridging experience

00:10:33.930 --> 00:10:37.770 align:middle line:84%
between the world of science
and the world of spirituality.

00:10:37.770 --> 00:10:39.900 align:middle line:84%
And it's a new technology
that a woman, who's

00:10:39.900 --> 00:10:43.140 align:middle line:84%
deeply spiritual but she's
an Italian neuroscientist,

00:10:43.140 --> 00:10:46.080 align:middle line:84%
created technology,
just a device,

00:10:46.080 --> 00:10:48.070 align:middle line:84%
like a lot of
neuromodulation devices.

00:10:48.070 --> 00:10:49.800 align:middle line:90%
But it's more refined.

00:10:49.800 --> 00:10:52.030 align:middle line:84%
And it operates
faster in real time.

00:10:52.030 --> 00:10:54.260 align:middle line:84%
And so as I'm going
through these little games,

00:10:54.260 --> 00:10:56.100 align:middle line:90%
I had a little headset on.

00:10:56.100 --> 00:10:58.400 align:middle line:84%
You're using your
mind-- it's wireless--

00:10:58.400 --> 00:11:00.120 align:middle line:84%
to play with your
computer screen

00:11:00.120 --> 00:11:02.530 align:middle line:84%
and change the reality on
the screen with your mind.

00:11:02.530 --> 00:11:04.090 align:middle line:90%
And it's happening in real time.

00:11:04.090 --> 00:11:10.290 align:middle line:84%
But what I noticed was the only
things that actually spiked

00:11:10.290 --> 00:11:13.770 align:middle line:84%
your levels of performance
to super coherent

00:11:13.770 --> 00:11:14.670 align:middle line:90%
were the feelings.

00:11:14.670 --> 00:11:16.650 align:middle line:90%
It wasn't your intention.

00:11:16.650 --> 00:11:18.210 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to move that thing.

00:11:18.210 --> 00:11:20.430 align:middle line:84%
You had to have an
intention that was clear.

00:11:20.430 --> 00:11:26.010 align:middle line:84%
But it was driven by the
feeling of love or gratitude.

00:11:26.010 --> 00:11:31.080 align:middle line:84%
Very specific kind of high
virtues of the spiritual world

00:11:31.080 --> 00:11:34.170 align:middle line:84%
would drive it into the
state of complete coherence.

00:11:34.170 --> 00:11:35.080 align:middle line:90%
And boom, boom, boom.

00:11:35.080 --> 00:11:38.310 align:middle line:84%
Now, your brain really
starts essentially creating

00:11:38.310 --> 00:11:42.870 align:middle line:84%
new neural networks and
raising its functionality.

00:11:42.870 --> 00:11:44.320 align:middle line:90%
But it was the two together.

00:11:44.320 --> 00:11:47.130 align:middle line:10%
>>FREKE: So I would
say the essential idea

00:11:47.130 --> 00:11:48.420 align:middle line:10%
in the philosophy--

00:11:48.420 --> 00:11:51.990 align:middle line:10%
I call it "unividualism," which
is in my book, "Soul Story"--

00:11:51.990 --> 00:11:56.080 align:middle line:10%
is that literally
everything has evolved.

00:11:56.080 --> 00:11:57.330 align:middle line:90%
That's the fundamental mantra.

00:11:57.330 --> 00:12:02.250 align:middle line:84%
Everything is the realization of
potentiality in deeper and more

00:12:02.250 --> 00:12:03.420 align:middle line:90%
emergent ways.

00:12:03.420 --> 00:12:08.190 align:middle line:84%
That's the hypothesis, so
that you can see the simplest

00:12:08.190 --> 00:12:09.060 align:middle line:90%
things start first.

00:12:09.060 --> 00:12:12.180 align:middle line:84%
So I love the current
scientific vision.

00:12:12.180 --> 00:12:14.010 align:middle line:84%
13.8 billion years
ago, all there

00:12:14.010 --> 00:12:16.070 align:middle line:90%
is is hydrogen and helium.

00:12:16.070 --> 00:12:19.950 align:middle line:84%
And that has become you and me
here, talking to each other,

00:12:19.950 --> 00:12:24.450 align:middle line:84%
through a steady process of
the realization of greater

00:12:24.450 --> 00:12:25.710 align:middle line:90%
and greater potentialities.

00:12:25.710 --> 00:12:26.877 align:middle line:90%
That's what the universe is.

00:12:26.877 --> 00:12:31.140 align:middle line:90%
It's a self-realizing process.

00:12:31.140 --> 00:12:32.908 align:middle line:84%
So what's the most
emergent thing?

00:12:32.908 --> 00:12:34.950 align:middle line:84%
Well, actually, I think
the most emergent thing--

00:12:34.950 --> 00:12:36.670 align:middle line:90%
the scientists would agree--

00:12:36.670 --> 00:12:38.920 align:middle line:84%
is this experience
we're having of psyche,

00:12:38.920 --> 00:12:42.403 align:middle line:84%
of a non-material realm of
ideas, which we're all having.

00:12:42.403 --> 00:12:44.070 align:middle line:84%
Well, the "psyche,"
that's a Greek word.

00:12:44.070 --> 00:12:44.870 align:middle line:90%
It means "soul."

00:12:44.870 --> 00:12:45.930 align:middle line:90%
This is the soul.

00:12:45.930 --> 00:12:49.110 align:middle line:84%
So even scientists
would agree, oh, we've

00:12:49.110 --> 00:12:51.360 align:middle line:90%
gone from hydrogen to the soul.

00:12:51.360 --> 00:12:54.520 align:middle line:84%
We've gone from basic matter to
something not made of matter.

00:12:54.520 --> 00:12:55.320 align:middle line:90%
And where is it?

00:12:55.320 --> 00:12:57.810 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't even exist in space.

00:12:57.810 --> 00:13:00.450 align:middle line:84%
And then the highest
thing in that, I think,

00:13:00.450 --> 00:13:04.530 align:middle line:84%
is the attention, consciousness,
and the love element

00:13:04.530 --> 00:13:06.810 align:middle line:90%
that you mentioned.

00:13:06.810 --> 00:13:07.860 align:middle line:90%
What--

00:13:07.860 --> 00:13:09.240 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Put
those two together,

00:13:09.240 --> 00:13:13.860 align:middle line:84%
and it's an incredibly
cohesive driving force.

00:13:13.860 --> 00:13:17.130 align:middle line:84%
>>FREKE: And what I think
this can explain is why.

00:13:17.130 --> 00:13:18.930 align:middle line:84%
That's what I'm
interested in, because it

00:13:18.930 --> 00:13:20.420 align:middle line:90%
seems to me the cutting edge.

00:13:20.420 --> 00:13:22.290 align:middle line:84%
We've arrived at
psyche, at soul.

00:13:22.290 --> 00:13:23.700 align:middle line:90%
And then we're conscious.

00:13:23.700 --> 00:13:24.720 align:middle line:90%
We've got intention.

00:13:24.720 --> 00:13:27.548 align:middle line:84%
And then what's happening is
that people are waking up--

00:13:27.548 --> 00:13:29.340 align:middle line:84%
and this is what the
deep spiritual message

00:13:29.340 --> 00:13:30.990 align:middle line:84%
is-- to the fact that
actually, they're

00:13:30.990 --> 00:13:32.835 align:middle line:90%
one with the whole universe.

00:13:32.835 --> 00:13:34.710 align:middle line:84%
They're moving from what
I call "individuals"

00:13:34.710 --> 00:13:36.810 align:middle line:84%
to "unividuals,"
who are individuals

00:13:36.810 --> 00:13:38.790 align:middle line:90%
conscious that everything's one.

00:13:38.790 --> 00:13:41.250 align:middle line:84%
And when that happens,
with this oneness,

00:13:41.250 --> 00:13:43.270 align:middle line:90%
there's this enormous love.

00:13:43.270 --> 00:13:45.120 align:middle line:84%
And that's what
motivates me and has

00:13:45.120 --> 00:13:48.060 align:middle line:84%
done since I was a little boy
is oh my god, I can wake up.

00:13:48.060 --> 00:13:50.490 align:middle line:84%
I'm one with universe, and
there's this incredible love.

00:13:50.490 --> 00:13:54.990 align:middle line:84%
So that looks to me like where
the whole process of evolution

00:13:54.990 --> 00:13:55.920 align:middle line:90%
has led.

00:13:55.920 --> 00:13:58.050 align:middle line:84%
So when you're sitting
there doing that process

00:13:58.050 --> 00:14:00.120 align:middle line:84%
and you're taking
loving attention--

00:14:00.120 --> 00:14:03.150 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And you're watching
through a physical device

00:14:03.150 --> 00:14:04.500 align:middle line:90%
the effects on the screen--

00:14:04.500 --> 00:14:05.250 align:middle line:84%
>>FREKE: You're seeing
what that does--

00:14:05.250 --> 00:14:06.875 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And then
you see the results.

00:14:06.875 --> 00:14:08.130 align:middle line:90%
>>FREKE: So you're seeing, ah.

00:14:08.130 --> 00:14:11.070 align:middle line:84%
So what we need to do is bring
the most emergent quality

00:14:11.070 --> 00:14:13.680 align:middle line:84%
in the universe, the
place it's all led to,

00:14:13.680 --> 00:14:16.960 align:middle line:84%
which is loving attention,
to all the issues we face.

00:14:16.960 --> 00:14:17.760 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:14:17.760 --> 00:14:19.920 align:middle line:84%
>>FREKE: And that's the
kind of sociological message

00:14:19.920 --> 00:14:21.253 align:middle line:90%
of this evolutionary philosophy.

00:14:21.253 --> 00:14:23.460 align:middle line:84%
It's like OK, this is
where we've got to.

00:14:23.460 --> 00:14:26.310 align:middle line:84%
We're changing from
individuals to "unividuals."

00:14:26.310 --> 00:14:28.072 align:middle line:90%
It's really happening a lot.

00:14:28.072 --> 00:14:30.030 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And this is
hard for a lot of people,

00:14:30.030 --> 00:14:32.850 align:middle line:84%
because a lot of times, people
who are brought into especially

00:14:32.850 --> 00:14:35.520 align:middle line:84%
a lot of the Eastern
traditions, for example,

00:14:35.520 --> 00:14:39.240 align:middle line:84%
are taking comfort in the notion
that they're not individuated,

00:14:39.240 --> 00:14:41.070 align:middle line:84%
that they're just
a drop in the sea,

00:14:41.070 --> 00:14:44.460 align:middle line:84%
and want to go back to becoming
just a drop in the hole,

00:14:44.460 --> 00:14:46.800 align:middle line:84%
without an individuated
I would say

00:14:46.800 --> 00:14:49.410 align:middle line:84%
not only consciousness but
sense of responsibility

00:14:49.410 --> 00:14:50.470 align:middle line:90%
and everything else.

00:14:50.470 --> 00:14:51.270 align:middle line:90%
>>FREKE: OK.

00:14:51.270 --> 00:14:55.020 align:middle line:84%
So I said, I'm asking
science to move,

00:14:55.020 --> 00:14:56.590 align:middle line:84%
and I'm asking
spirituality to move.

00:14:56.590 --> 00:14:58.530 align:middle line:84%
So with science,
what I'm saying is,

00:14:58.530 --> 00:15:00.960 align:middle line:84%
look, with the current
evolutionary story, which

00:15:00.960 --> 00:15:04.170 align:middle line:84%
is immense, it goes up
to the evolution of life.

00:15:04.170 --> 00:15:05.700 align:middle line:84%
And then there's
this side effect

00:15:05.700 --> 00:15:08.400 align:middle line:90%
we call the "soul," the psyche.

00:15:08.400 --> 00:15:10.410 align:middle line:84%
I'm saying to
science, no, no, no.

00:15:10.410 --> 00:15:12.810 align:middle line:84%
There's a whole other
phase of evolution,

00:15:12.810 --> 00:15:15.060 align:middle line:84%
which is the evolution of
the soul, which spirituality

00:15:15.060 --> 00:15:17.550 align:middle line:90%
has always been about.

00:15:17.550 --> 00:15:19.490 align:middle line:90%
Don't end the story.

00:15:19.490 --> 00:15:21.020 align:middle line:90%
The story's one story.

00:15:21.020 --> 00:15:23.120 align:middle line:90%
It reaches further.

00:15:23.120 --> 00:15:27.170 align:middle line:84%
If we can see that, then we
can make it one understanding.

00:15:27.170 --> 00:15:30.170 align:middle line:84%
Then to spirituality,
most ancient spirituality

00:15:30.170 --> 00:15:31.950 align:middle line:90%
works with the myth of the fall.

00:15:31.950 --> 00:15:34.580 align:middle line:84%
Everything was great, and
then we fell into life.

00:15:34.580 --> 00:15:36.480 align:middle line:90%
We're trapped in the body.

00:15:36.480 --> 00:15:38.070 align:middle line:90%
The life is an illusion.

00:15:38.070 --> 00:15:39.440 align:middle line:90%
It's a bad thing.

00:15:39.440 --> 00:15:42.590 align:middle line:84%
Even your individuality is in
the way of you, like a drop,

00:15:42.590 --> 00:15:43.820 align:middle line:90%
going back to the ocean--

00:15:43.820 --> 00:15:45.770 align:middle line:90%
totally anti-life.

00:15:45.770 --> 00:15:47.423 align:middle line:90%
It's a negative view.

00:15:47.423 --> 00:15:48.590 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I agree with that.

00:15:48.590 --> 00:15:49.640 align:middle line:90%
>>FREKE: It's just an old view.

00:15:49.640 --> 00:15:50.320 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I agree with that.

00:15:50.320 --> 00:15:52.580 align:middle line:84%
>>FREKE: There was a
time it was cutting-edge.

00:15:52.580 --> 00:15:54.350 align:middle line:84%
By getting rid of
that idea of the fall

00:15:54.350 --> 00:15:56.970 align:middle line:84%
and replacing it with this
beautiful optimistic story

00:15:56.970 --> 00:15:58.980 align:middle line:90%
of evolution, of emergence--

00:15:58.980 --> 00:16:03.417 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But not evolution
as we know it from Darwinism.

00:16:03.417 --> 00:16:04.250 align:middle line:10%
>>FREKE: Darwinism--

00:16:04.250 --> 00:16:05.270 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: Darwinism--

00:16:05.270 --> 00:16:07.810 align:middle line:10%
>>FREKE: Darwinism
and also Wallace,

00:16:07.810 --> 00:16:12.860 align:middle line:10%
it was incredible insight that
what they saw was all of life

00:16:12.860 --> 00:16:14.810 align:middle line:10%
had evolved from a simple cell.

00:16:14.810 --> 00:16:15.650 align:middle line:90%
What a vision.

00:16:15.650 --> 00:16:17.750 align:middle line:84%
How that happens, we're
still working it out

00:16:17.750 --> 00:16:18.900 align:middle line:90%
and all the rest of it.

00:16:18.900 --> 00:16:21.440 align:middle line:90%
But it looks like it's happened.

00:16:21.440 --> 00:16:23.060 align:middle line:90%
What a mind-blowing vision.

00:16:23.060 --> 00:16:24.740 align:middle line:90%
All of life is one thing.

00:16:24.740 --> 00:16:28.380 align:middle line:10%
And then 100 years ago, with
big bang theory, oh my god.

00:16:28.380 --> 00:16:31.400 align:middle line:10%
There's a whole 10 billion
years before that, in which

00:16:31.400 --> 00:16:35.300 align:middle line:10%
the whole universe has evolved.

00:16:35.300 --> 00:16:37.175 align:middle line:10%
But there's no
Darwinism in then.

00:16:37.175 --> 00:16:38.300 align:middle line:10%
That's a different process.

00:16:38.300 --> 00:16:38.660 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:16:38.660 --> 00:16:40.368 align:middle line:84%
But then there are
the ancient mysteries.

00:16:40.368 --> 00:16:45.280 align:middle line:84%
It's everything evolved once a
template was set into motion.

00:16:45.280 --> 00:16:46.240 align:middle line:90%
>>FREKE: Yeah.

00:16:46.240 --> 00:16:47.990 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That gets
more complicated then.

00:16:47.990 --> 00:16:48.790 align:middle line:90%
>>FREKE: It does.

00:16:48.790 --> 00:16:53.180 align:middle line:84%
And my own understanding
of how that process works

00:16:53.180 --> 00:16:56.700 align:middle line:84%
is to do with the
nature of time.

00:16:56.700 --> 00:16:59.743 align:middle line:84%
So when I study time
experientially, as well as

00:16:59.743 --> 00:17:01.160 align:middle line:84%
philosophically,
I look at it now.

00:17:01.160 --> 00:17:03.050 align:middle line:90%
And I go, oh, it's interesting.

00:17:03.050 --> 00:17:04.869 align:middle line:84%
Every moment I've
ever experienced

00:17:04.869 --> 00:17:06.829 align:middle line:90%
has got two qualities.

00:17:06.829 --> 00:17:08.670 align:middle line:84%
One, it realizes a
new potentiality,

00:17:08.670 --> 00:17:10.170 align:middle line:84%
because that's what
the universe is.

00:17:10.170 --> 00:17:11.900 align:middle line:84%
It's always realizing,
oh, this is new.

00:17:11.900 --> 00:17:12.859 align:middle line:90%
Never had this before.

00:17:12.859 --> 00:17:13.910 align:middle line:90%
Great.

00:17:13.910 --> 00:17:15.619 align:middle line:84%
And also-- and this
is the key bit--

00:17:15.619 --> 00:17:19.430 align:middle line:84%
